# Matex Financial Integrity Rules

## The Golden Rule: All Payments Flow Through Escrow
**No money moves directly between buyer and seller.** Every purchase creates an `escrow_mcp.escrows` record first.
```
Order confirmed
  → escrow created (status: created)
  → buyer funds charged via Stripe PI (status: funds_held)
  → goods delivered + inspection approved
  → escrow released to seller (status: released)
  → Matex commission deducted before payout
```

## Commission Structure
| Transaction Type | Rate | Minimum Fee | Cap |
|---|---|---|---|
| Standard Sale | 3.5% | $25 CAD | $5,000 CAD |
| Auction Sale | 4.0% | $50 CAD | $7,500 CAD |
| Featured Listing | $49.99/month | N/A | N/A |
| Premium Seller Subscription | $199/month | — | Reduces rate to 2.5% / $3,500 cap |
| Carrier Commission | 5% of freight | $15 CAD | $1,000 CAD |

GST/HST applies to the commission amount — store in `payments_mcp.transactions.tax_amount`.

## Commission Adjustment Rules
- Base commission is calculated on the **original agreed amount** at time of sale/close.
- **Weight discrepancy adjustment**: If final weight differs >tolerance, recalculate on adjusted amount.
- **Quality deduction adjustment**: Recalculate on net amount after inspection deduction.
- **Dispute refund adjustment**: Partial refund → recalculate on settled amount. Full refund → reverse commission entirely.
- **Adjustment window**: Only within 30 days of original transaction. After 30 days, original commission is final.
- **Minimum floor always applies**: Even after adjustments, the minimum commission fee still applies.
- Set `commission_adjusted = true` and populate `adjustment_reason` on any recalculation.

## Down Payment Schedule (by transaction value)
| Transaction Value | Down Payment | Balance | Payment Stages |
|---|---|---|---|
| < $5,000 CAD | 100% upfront | N/A | Single payment |
| $5,000 – $25,000 | 25% down | 75% before shipping | 2-stage |
| $25,000 – $100,000 | 20% down | 80% in installments | 3-stage (20/40/40) |
| > $100,000 | 15% down | 85% per milestone | Custom (negotiated) |

Milestones are stored in `payments_mcp.down_payment_schedules.milestones` (JSONB array with `milestone`, `pct`, `amount`, `due_date`, `status`, `paid_at`).

## Escrow Release Conditions
Never release escrow unless ALL applicable `release_conditions` are met:
- `inspection_approved: true` (if listing had `inspection_required = true`)
- `delivery_confirmed: true` (POD uploaded to `logistics_mcp.shipments`)
- `dispute_resolved: true` (if a dispute was opened against the order)

## Wallet Constraints
- `payments_mcp.wallets.balance` has `CHECK (balance >= 0)` — this is a hard DB constraint; never bypass.
- `pending_balance` tracks in-transit funds; never merge into `balance` before settlement.
- Wallet top-ups: `transaction_type = 'wallet_topup'`.

## Transaction Type Reference
| Type | When to Use |
|---|---|
| `purchase` | Buyer payment for an order |
| `deposit` | General deposit to wallet |
| `bid_deposit` | Refundable deposit to participate in auction |
| `refund` | Returning funds to buyer |
| `commission` | Matex platform commission deduction |
| `payout` | Releasing funds to seller |
| `wallet_topup` | Adding funds to user wallet |
| `credit_payment` | Repayment of credit facility |
| `penalty` | Financial penalty imposed via dispute |
| `adjustment` | Manual correction — requires `adjustment_reason` |

## Credit Facility Rules
| Tier | Requirements | Credit Limit | Terms |
|---|---|---|---|
| `none` | Default | $0 (escrow only) | 100% upfront |
| `basic` | KYC level_2 + 3 txns + PIS > 70 | $25,000 | Net 15 |
| `standard` | 6mo active + 10 txns + PIS > 80 + financials | $100,000 | Net 30 |
| `premium` | 12mo + 25 txns + PIS > 90 + audited financials | $500,000 | Net 60 |
| `enterprise` | Custom assessment + $1M+ annual volume | Up to $2M | Net 90 |

- Available credit = `credit_limit − total_outstanding`. Never allow drawdown beyond `available_credit`.
- Matex Credit Score (MCS) range: 300–850.
- Late payment interest: 1.5%/month (`interest_rate_monthly = 0.0150`).
- After 15 days overdue: freeze credit facility. After 30 days: collections process.
- Every score change writes to `credit_mcp.credit_score_history` with `factors` JSONB.

## Weight-Based Price Adjustments
- Default weight tolerance: ±2% (material-specific tolerances override this).
- Reference weight priority: `w4_third_party` > `w3_buyer` > `w2_carrier` > `w1_seller`.
- `w4_third_party` (CAW-certified re-weigh) is binding in disputes.
- If actual weight differs beyond tolerance, recalculate `orders_mcp.orders.adjusted_amount`.

## Bid Deposits
- Losing bidders' deposits must be refunded within 24 hours of auction close.
- Winner's deposit is applied toward the purchase — never double-charged.

## Tax Reporting (T5018)
`tax-mcp` auto-generates T5018 (Statement of Contract Payments) for any seller receiving >$500 in a calendar year. This is a CRA compliance requirement — it cannot be skipped.

## Seller Payout Timing
Seller is paid within 7 days of confirmed delivery (when Matex assumes credit risk under trade credit terms). Standard escrow release: after buyer inspection window closes (48–72 hours).
